title: Unnecessary parentheses around argument lint

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-beta
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to beta.

body:
**This is likely going to be closed as expected breakage. This means those cc-ed below should probably aim to fix their crate and release a new point release.**

Due to https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/46980.

 - [cargo 0.24.0](http://cargobomb-reports.s3.amazonaws.com/stable-1.24.0-beta-1.25.0-beta.2/beta-2018-02-20/reg/cargo-0.24.0/log.txt) cc @alexcrichton 
 - [alga 0.5.2](https://crates.io/crates/alga/0.5.2) (fixed on alga master, not yet released, cc @sebcrozet)
 - [fluxcap 0.0.5](http://cargobomb-reports.s3.amazonaws.com/stable-1.24.0-beta-1.25.0-beta.2/beta-2018-02-20/reg/fluxcap-0.0.5/log.txt) cc @rodolf0
 - [hdrhistogram 6.0.3](http://cargobomb-reports.s3.amazonaws.com/stable-1.24.0-beta-1.25.0-beta.2/beta-2018-02-20/reg/hdrhistogram-6.0.3/log.txt) cc @jonhoo

Estimated ecosystem breakage: 3603 versions (4.41% versions published), 551 crates (3.85% of crates). Though technically most/all of this will be fine because of cap lints.
